            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>ground cumin </strong>to the pan with the <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>smoked paprika </strong>and<strong> cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>beef stock mix</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
